Function: Takes in a file of the form;
[num points]
[num triangles]
<x1> <y1> <z1>
.
.
<pt_a> <pt_b> <pt_c>
.
.
and draws the coresponding polygon using
efficient triangle drawing and a z-buffer.
The functionality allows you to rotate the model
about it's y-axis.

usage:
[program].out [input file name]

controls:
a-rotate left
d-rotate right
w-toggle wireframe
